		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have a set but they are not reliable, the keyboard often stops on you even with new batteries. The mouse is not very accurate and the surfaces it will work on is limited.
<br />
<br />
<br />The computer site I usually ask questions on has been down for a wile now and you guys know your stuff so I decided I would ask you.
<br />
<br />I would rather not spend a huge amount of money but I need something dependable, I’m tired of looking back up at the screen (since I cannot type without looking at the keyboard) and seeing nothing on the screen and I’m tired of having to fight my mouse to get it to do what I want. I guess going to walmart and getting the cheapest one they have is not always the best idea.
<br />
<br />Also note I usually use the mouse on the arm of a lazy boy recliner.
<br />
<br />So some advice would be great here.

		

